Blurb::
Specify a scalar data file to complement field data files (mixed case)

Description::

When calibrating both scalar and field calibration terms, to
associated experimental data, the scalar data may be provided in the
file named by \c scalar_data_file.  This file follows the same format
as: \ref responses-calibration_terms-calibration_data_file.

<b> Default Behavior </b>

If \c scalar_data_file is omitted, all calibration data, including for
scalar responses, will be read from the generic field \c
calibration_data format.

